Feeling blessed, honored, and ooooh so very thankful to the people that made me and @broadythejoker vision come to fruition. *For y’all that have been hitting me up about getting my own podcast… it’s finally about that time!

First, @youlovepaper our executive producer who heard my pitch after I appeared on Quake’s House and said “lemme help make this happen!” Less than a week later… we’re filming a show @dashradio for his @tastemakers.radio. When the timing is right, everything falls into place. 🙏🏾🙏🏾

@dedomatic & @mask.504 my men behind the cameras who were able to roll through the technical difficulties with breeze. Thanks for answering my call and being all in, prepared, reliable, and providing super dope energy. 💛💛

To our guests!! @suavetheauthor @persephanii @diceyapproved OMG! We couldn’t have shot a better 1st episode. Thank you for being so open, honest, sharing, sexy, and freakin hilarious. 😂😂

And to my co-host and brother @broadythejoker Dude, we did it!! 1 down, many to go!! 

Some of y’all know how I move and for those that don’t… when I produce a project I’m VERY detail oriented. I try to think ahead for every possible fire that could occur, so if and when it happens, I’m prepared to make the shift so the show can go on without too much of a delay. That said, it causes major anxiety yet there’s such a relief when it’s finished, and after putting this together in 3 days… I’m just feeling the relief and utter gratitude to all involved. ❤️❤️❤️ to you all! 

More on the project coming next month! For now, go follow @funnyfuxpodcast @dashradio @tastemakers.radio
